// Correctness arc 13 (s): a compound literal constant folds-then-checks
// against the declared type — `var a int8 = 100 + 100` silently stored
// -56 (per-leaf range checks only: each 100 individually fits). The
// adapter now judges the folded value of an unambiguous compound (not
// negated-rooted, fold below the modular [2^63,2^64) window) via the
// shared representability rule. Go rejects: 200 overflows int8.
package main

func main() {
	var a int8 = 100 + 100
	println(a)
}
